{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[Csus2] There is freedom within,[Am] there is freedom without.
[F] Try to catch the deluge in a paper [E]cup.  [Esus4]
[Csus2] There's a battle ahead,[Am] many battles are lost
[F] But you'll never see the end of the road while you're [E]travelin' with me.
{end_of_verse}


{start_of_chorus: Chorus}
[F] Hey now, [G]hey now
Don't [C]dream it's [Am]over.
[F] Hey now, [G]hey now
When the [C]world comes i[Am]n.
The[F]y come, they[G] come
[C] To build a wall bet[Am]ween us.
[F] We know they won't win.  [G]
{end_of_chorus}


{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[Csus2] Now I'm towing my car,[Am] there's a hole in the roof.
[F] My possessions are causing me suspicion but [E]there's no proof.
[Csus2] In the paper today,[Am] tales of war and of waste
[F] But you turn right over to the T.V. [G]page.
{end_of_verse}


{start_of_chorus: Chorus}
[F] Hey now, [G]hey now
Don't [C]dream it's [Am]over.
[F] Hey now, [G]hey now
When the [C]world comes i[Am]n.
The[F]y come, they[G] come
[C] To build a wall bet[Am]ween us.
[F] We know they won't win. (plus 2/4 measure)
{end_of_chorus}


